# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Here, We can see there is a sequence a --> b --> c --> d, a is richer than b, b richer than c and so on. We can also observe one thing that the richest person cannot have anyone more quiet than him with more money. So, the answer for the richest will be the same person itself. So, we begin with the richest person (i.e in graph terms we can say that their indegree will be zero)
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We can use Kahn's algorithm to traverse the graph(persons) and updating their quietness and the answer array at the same time.

