# Intuition
The main thing would be here is to construct the adjacency list as it only provides the way forward to traverse through the richer people than the current people and find the quietest among them.

In order to construct the adjacency matrix we have to relate them reverse so that someone who is poor is always having the richer person in the adjacency list in order for him to traverse and find the richer people than him.

`adj[richer[i][1]].push_back(richer[i][0])`

# Approach
Once after creating the adjacency list we can actually traverse by using DFS for each index and if we have already found the answer during the previous search then we simply return the answer and fill the answer array.
This approach is also called as Hashing the DFS such that we might not move through the already found answer instead if we have the answer already hashed we simply return it.
