# Intuition
For any person, we look for all the person who is equally rich or richer than them and then we select the quietest among these set of richer people.

# Approach
Here, we use **topological sort** to find the least quiet person among all people who definitely have equal to or more money than the person.

![WhatsApp Image 2023-05-27 at 10.21.47.jpg](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/ea093f1d-efc2-4b18-af15-7828d17cd019_1685163806.2208238.jpeg)


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(V+E), since it is directed graph.

- Space complexity:
O(3V)~O(V), since we have queue, indegree array and ans array.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> loudAndRich(vector<vector<int>>& richer, vector<int>& quiet) {
        int n=quiet.size();
        vector<int>ans(n);
        vector<int>indeg(n,0);
        vector<int>adj[n];

        for(auto it:richer){ 
            //adjacentcy list for matrix richer
            adj[it[0]].push_back(it[1]);
            indeg[it[1]]++;
        }

        queue<int>q;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            //assigning all ans[i] to i which will be updated later after comparision, we can also assign it to some negative number.
            ans[i]=i;

            // for each i, if indegree is 0 push it into q;
            if(indeg[i]==0){
                q.push(i);
            }
        }

        while(!q.empty()){
            int node=q.front();
            q.pop();

            for(auto it:adj[node]){
                //comparing the values of adjacent node values and current node in quiet array and upadting it.
                if(quiet[ans[node]]<quiet[ans[it]]){
                    ans[it]=ans[node];
                }

                indeg[it]--;
                if(indeg[it]==0){
                    q.push(it);
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

