There are basically 2 ways in which the tilings can turn out, 
that is discussed below in **Figure 1 & 2** :

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/16e54aad-bfe6-4c72-bb39-9503ddebc73c_1597410834.434251.png)





This is the **Default way** where we take the largest possible tile that can fit.
And further solve for the white rectangle with dimensions (m-n) x n.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/588dda42-c356-4e93-8a0e-d01c79f0db1e_1597408105.3532898.png)



Here in **Figure 2**
    the blue portions are filled with tiles of dimensions s x s and k x k.
    we have to further solve for rectangles **rect1,rect2 & rect3** in colors **pink,yellow & green** respectively.

 Note: In the below code 
        1) All variables are used in according to figure 2
        2) In all cases n<=m.

Dimensions of the rectangles
**rect1 : b x (m-k)
rect2 : X x Y
rect3 : (n-k) x a**

Given below are all the states for :
**n=11 & m=13 & s=7**
**Note**
**1) rect2 is with red boundary
2) at State 3 the tile k x k overflows the are a x b**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/e3031583-5a5f-49e0-b5e2-52e3ad37bb15_1597411186.7207372.png)


	class Solution {
	public:    
		vector<vector<int>> memo;
		int solve(int n,int m)
		{
			if(memo[n][m]!=-1)
				return memo[n][m];
			if(n==m)
				return 1;
			else if(n==0 || m==0)
				return 0;
			else if(n==1)
				return m;
			int nextn=min(n,m);
			int nextm=max(n,m)-nextn;
			int res=solve(min(nextn,nextm),max(nextn,nextm))+1;     // Default way in Figure 1
			for(int s=nextn-1;s>0;--s)
			{
				int a=max(abs(n-s),abs(m-s));       //larger side
				int b=min(abs(n-s),abs(m-s));       //smaller side
				for(int k=b;k<=a && k<=n;++k)
				{
					int x=min(abs(a-k),abs(b-k)),y=max(abs(a-k),abs(b-k));
					int rect1=solve(min(b,m-k),max(b,m-k));
					int rect2=solve(x,y);
					int rect3=solve(min(n-k,a),max(n-k,a));
					int ans=2+rect1+rect2+rect3;        // here 2 is addded for the 2 rectangle sxs and kxk
					res=min(res,ans);
				}
			}
			memo[n][m]=res;
			return res;
		}
		int tilingRectangle(int n, int m)
		{
			int x=min(n,m),y=max(n,m);
			memo.resize(x+1);
			for(auto& v:memo)
				v.resize(y+1,-1);
			return solve(x,y);
		}
	};

