This dp considers the state of matrix after you add a square. Initially when no squares are added, matrix is empty. When we add a square some of the heights change. We need to find all combinations for that state. 
Example: 3x2 matrix
lets consider ht as 3 and base as 2;
* Initially the height at each index of the base is 0, because we have no squares.
* Find the left Most Index with minimum height/depression.(Initially its 0,0)
* We are adding squares to fill the gaps with all the squares possible.
* We then start adding sqs of valid length to this depression.(which are 1 and 2 because we cant exceed 2)
* Update the height list which the new square has altered.
* Our recursion ends when the list min height is equal to the height of the matrix(meaning full);

The code is below:
```
class Solution {

    //dp map to store the visited structure
    Map<List<Integer>,Integer> map ;


    public int tilingRectangle(int n, int m) {
        map = new HashMap<List<Integer>,Integer>();
        List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<Integer>();
        for(int i = 0;i<m;i++)
            list.add(0);
        return backTrack(list,n);
    }

    int backTrack(List<Integer> list,int n){
        if(map.get(list) != null)
            return map.get(list);

        int ans = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        //find the minDepth 
        int startIndex = findMinDepthIndex(list);
        //if you have reached the height its the exit case
        if(list.get(startIndex) == n)
            return 0;
        int endIndex = startIndex;
        //adding the square till its valid
        while(endIndex<list.size() && (endIndex-startIndex+1)<=n-list.get(startIndex) && list.get(endIndex)==list.get(startIndex)){
            int length = endIndex - startIndex +1;
            for(int i =startIndex;i<=endIndex;i++)
                list.set(i,length+list.get(i));

            ans = Math.min(ans,1+backTrack(list,n));

            for(int i =startIndex;i<=endIndex;i++)
                list.set(i,list.get(i)-length);      
            endIndex++;
        }
        map.put(new ArrayList<Integer>(list),ans);
        return map.get(list);
    }

    int findMinDepthIndex(List<Integer> list){
        int minHt = 0;
        for(int i =0;i<list.size();i++){
            if(list.get(i)<list.get(minHt))
                minHt = i;
        }

        return minHt;
    }
}

```

