solutions.content:
recursive DP + greedy

Any rect(n, m) (n <= m) can be processed as 
(1) one square m = n; 
(2) one square(i, i) + one L shape(m-i, i, i, n - i) 1<i<n; 
(3) one square(n, n) + one rect(n, m - n).

Any L shape(l1, l2, l3, l4) can be processed as
(1) one square + one rect(l3 + l1, l4) l1 ==l2;
(2) one square + one rect(l1, l2 + l4) l3 == l4;
(3) one square + one L shape(l1, l2-l1,l3,l4) l2 > l1;
(4) one square + one L shape(l4 + l2 - l1, l1, l1 - l2, l3) l2 < l1;
(5) one square + one L shape(l1, l2, l3 - l4, l4) l3 > l4;
(6) one square + one L shape(l1 + l3 - l4, l4, l4 - l3, l2) l3 < l4.
     ___________________
l1 |                                                |
     |________                           |
               l2	     |                           |
                           |                           |
					l3   |                           |
						   |__________|
                                     l4


