```

---------------------------------------------------------

**Backtracking solution**

After view some other posts like [this one from @kevincabbage](https://leetcode.com/problems/tiling-a-rectangle-with-the-fewest-squares/discuss/414329/DFS), the backtracking method would give correct solution.

Our method is to backtracking each enums to search best solution, so how to solve this problem?
1. suppose the top-left position at (0, 0)
2. each recursion, search for the top-left unfilled cell, and try to fill bigger square.
	suppose the position is at **(top, left)**, so the possible length of square is in **[1, min{n-top, m-left}]**, just enumerate each possible length.
3. continue to backtrack

important optimization:
* when enumerate the length of square, we should select from **min{n-top, m-left}** to 1,  because the optimal solution would appear earily.
* we can return easily if the current num is bigger than previous num. (followed by the first point)

```
public static class Solution {
	// record the optimal solution
	private int res;
	public int tilingRectangle(int n, int m) {
		boolean[][] matrix = new boolean[n][m];    // m*n cells, true means filled, false means unfilled 表示m*n个单元格，false表示未填充
		res = m*n;  // initilazation, all 1 cell to fill
		DFS(matrix, 0, m*n);
		return res;
	}
	/*
	matrix means the cells of n*m
	curNum means the current nums of square
	leftNum means the num of left cells
	*/
	private void DFS(boolean[][] matrix,  int curNum, int leftNum) {
		// pruning
		if (curNum >= res) return;
		// finish till
		if (leftNum == 0) {
			res = Math.min(curNum, res);
			return;
		}
		// find left-top unfilled position
		int left = 0, top;
		for (top = 0; top < matrix.length; ++top) {
			for (left = 0; left < matrix[0].length; ++left) {
				if (!matrix[top][left]) break;
			}
			if (left < matrix[0].length) break;
		}
		// try all size square from large to small
		int len = 1; // enum the length of square
		for (len = Math.min(matrix.length-top, matrix[0].length-left); len >= 1; --len) {
			// check if the len is valid
			boolean valid = true;
			for (int i = top; i < top+len; ++i) {
				for (int j = left; j < left+len; ++j) {
					if (matrix[i][j]) {
						valid = false;
					}
				}
				if (!valid) break;
			}
			if (!valid) continue;
			// fill
			for (int i = top; i < top+len; ++i) {
				for (int j = left; j < left + len; ++j) {
					matrix[i][j] = true;
				}
			}
			DFS(matrix, curNum+1, leftNum-len*len);
			// unfill
			for (int i = top; i < top+len; ++i) {
				for (int j = left; j < left + len; ++j) {
					matrix[i][j] = false;
				}
			}
		}
	}
}
```

