# Daily Challenge:-19/02/2022.
**Approach**:-We take help of Set.
Basic about Set:-Set is Binary Search tree Based STL container in c++..
As we know,The values in set are stored in a specific order.

**What Actually We are doing**:-
**Step1:-**
-->Firstly we convert every odd element to even by multiplying it by two.
This is because we avoid Calculation Part for odd element.
-->Now all the elements of array is even.
-->Then we store this Element in set.

**Step2:-**
-->We know that for any array Deviation is difference btween maximum element of array and minimum element of array.
-->so,To minimize our deviation. We should make our maximum value of array as much close to minimum value.

**Now ,understand what we are doing inside while loop:-**
*Before that I want to explain two things.*
1.) begin():-Returns an iterator to the first element in the set. Tc=O(log(n))
2.) rbegin():-Returns a reverse iterator pointing to the last element in the container. Tc=O(log(n))
As we know set store element in sorted order.
So, value at  begin() is minimum value in set.
and value at rbegin is maximum value of set.

One more thing you should know ,that ,In C++ Set doesn't allow us to modify any value.
Insted of that you can remove that value and insert the modified value.

**Now,Understand What Happening inside while loop.**
-->We calculate the deviation for that itration.(Calculating the difference btween maximum and minimum.)
-->Compare it with minimum deviation.-->Upgrade our minimum deviation.

**Now,**
-->If our maximum value in set is Even means We can futher Reduce it.
-->So we divide it by two.
And We insert that modified vlaue in set.
After this Calculation Maximum value of set will Change,And It is always not necessary that It become previous maximum_value/2.


-->Else if our maximum value is Odd ,Means We can't further minimize our Maximum value.
So we break the Loop.

In the End return our minimum deviation value.

Worst caseTime Complexity= O(nlog(n));
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeviation(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size();
        set<int>maxh; //Set for calculation.
        /*Step1:-Making Every odd element even. And storing all the element in set.*/
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if((nums[i]&1)!=0)
                maxh.insert(nums[i]*2);
            else
                maxh.insert(nums[i]);
        }

        /*Step2*/
        int mn_deviation=INT_MAX;
        while(true)
        {
           int deviation=(*(maxh.rbegin())-*(maxh.begin())); //store the deviation

            mn_deviation=min(mn_deviation,deviation); //Update our minimum deviation.

            int max_value=*(maxh.rbegin()); //Maximum value.
            if((max_value & 1)==0)
            {
                /*If maximum value is Even,Minimize it further.*/
                maxh.erase(max_value);
                maxh.insert(max_value/2);
            }
            else
                break;
        }
            return mn_deviation;
    }
};
```
