class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeviation(vector<int>& nums) {
        /*
        since we need to find the minimum deviation, there are two things that 
        we can certainly do : minimize the max and maximize the min.
        Agree???
        Now the real deal is how to find this max and how to find this min?

        Now you know that if the number is odd, you have to multiply it by 2
        and this is the only way to maximize the odd number. After multiplying the odd
        by 2, you are not allowed to furthur multiply coz now its even number now
        and even number can only be divided by 2. (refer to the first for  loop in the code )

        So till this point you have maximized all the odd numbers. Why maximize
        all the odd numbers because i told you that you have to maximize
        every number possible and here in this problem the possibility of maximizing
        the numbers lies with the case of odd numbers.

        and while doing this maximization step, we will keep finding our minimum
        value. Notice here that in minimum value , we will be having minimal even
        number. Do you agree?

        Now here comes the part of minimization, now which values you can minimize?
        Those values which are even . Correct??

        And you will say, that at this moment, all values present in the array are
        even and i wiil say yes you are right.
		At this point , things may not  make some sense. But keep reading thoroughly ,
		you will understand it.
        Now we will put these values in the max heap so that we can always get the
        maximum number by doing o(1) operation and we will keep dividing this 
        maximum number by 2 and will keep a note of min deviation.We will stop to 
        a point where the max value is odd coz it can not be minimized further.

        Lets jump to the code to make some sense out of this story.
        */
        priority_queue<int>max_heap;
        //step 1 : maximization
        int minimum_value=INT_MAX;
        for(int i =0;i<nums.size();i++){
            if(nums[i] &1){ //that is odd 
                nums[i]*=2;
            }
            //keeping a check on minimum value
            minimum_value=min(minimum_value,nums[i]);
            max_heap.push(nums[i]);
        }
        //after this loop every element present in array will be even
        int deviation=INT_MAX;
        //step 2 : Minimization
        //every time we will pick up the maximum value , will calculate the
        //deviation and will minimize it
        while(!max_heap.empty() && max_heap.top()%2==0){
            int maximum_value=max_heap.top();
            max_heap.pop();
            deviation=min(deviation,maximum_value-minimum_value);
            //check if we have another minimum_value when we divide this no. by 2
            minimum_value=min(minimum_value,maximum_value/2);
            max_heap.push(maximum_value/2);

        }
        return min(deviation, max_heap.top()-minimum_value);

    }
};

