<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The intuition is quite simple. We need to find max Deviation which is nothing but maxEle-minEle. 
This is too basic. We only need to minimize this deviation and we have infinite operations. So relax, think how you can decrease the max and increase the min. :)
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Implementation part is a bit tricky, but when we see the words min and max, we may think of something called HEAP. So lets build it!
1. We know that if ele is odd, we can multiply it by 2, and this will make the ele even. So lets push all ele in maxHeap, and if ele is odd, multiply by 2 and then push.
2. Make sure you also keep a track of the miniVal while pushing in heap
3. Now see the ele at top of heap, and calc the deviation i.e. `maxVal-minVal` do this and store minDev.
4. Divide maxVal by 2 and again push in heap
5. Here also keep track of minVal
6. Now if the maxVal comes out to be odd, then you need to break, as we cannot further divide it by 2 as odd num cannot produce whole num when divided by 2
7. Keep doing this and once we finish the loop, return minDev
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(nlogn)
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
