# Intuition
1. Insert the elements of vector in a set(elements will be ordered and only once in a set).
2. Create two iterators start and last and an integer variable min_ans where min_ans=*last -*start.

3. update *start=*start*2 until*start%2!=0, so that smallest element will become even and cant be increased further. In each iteration update start again to set.begin(). And at each iteration calculate differnce of last and first element and update min_ans to min of differnce and min_ans.
4. Then update *last=*last/2 until *last%2==0, so that larget element will be divided. again update min_ans accordingly.
5. return min_ans;



# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(n)

- Space complexity:O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeviation(vector<int>& nums) {
        set<int> sorted_nums;
        for(auto num: nums){
            sorted_nums.insert(num);
        }
        set<int>:: iterator start=sorted_nums.begin();
        set<int>:: reverse_iterator last=sorted_nums.rbegin();
        int min_ans=*last-*start;
        while(*start%2!=0){
            int t=*start;
            sorted_nums.erase(t);
            sorted_nums.insert(2*t);
            start=sorted_nums.begin();
            int ans=*last-*start;
            min_ans=min(ans,min_ans);
        }
        while(*last%2==0){
            int t=*last;
            sorted_nums.erase(t);
            sorted_nums.insert(t/2);
            start=sorted_nums.begin();
            int ans=*last-*start;
            min_ans=min(ans,min_ans);
        }

        return min_ans;
    }
};
```

