# Approach
find the difference of minimum even element to maximun odd element in priority queue.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(nlognlogm)   // m = maximum elemenet

- Space complexity:
O(n) 

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minimumDeviation(int[] nums) {
        PriorityQueue<Integer> pq = new PriorityQueue<>((a,b) -> (b-a));
        int minValue = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for(int num : nums){
            if(num%2 != 0){
                num = 2*num;
            }
            minValue = Math.min(minValue, num);
            pq.add(num);
        }
        int n = nums.length;
        int diff = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        while(pq.peek() %2 == 0){
            int maxTill = pq.poll();
            diff = Math.min(diff, maxTill-minValue);
            minValue = Math.min(minValue, maxTill / 2);
            pq.add(maxTill/2);
        }
        return Math.min(diff, pq.peek()-minValue);
    }
}
```

